        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Suggestions: laa1"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "To make a suggestion or a request (like 'Let's...' in English), add <strong>啦</strong> (laa1) to the end of a verb. This is softer and more natural than just stating the action."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "講啦",
          "romanization": "gong2 laa1",
          "translation": "Speak (suggestion) / Say it"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "去啦",
          "romanization": "heoi3 laa1",
          "translation": "Let's go / Go (suggestion)"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The Bounce Back: ne1"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "When you want to 'bounce' a question back to the other person, add <strong>呢</strong> (ne1) to a noun or pronoun. It's the standard way to say 'And...?' or 'What about...?'."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "你呢？",
          "romanization": "nei5 ne1?",
          "translation": "And you? / What about you?"
        }
      ]
    },
